name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: mapreduce.shuffle.listen.queue.size
description: The length of the shuffle server listen queue.

name: dfs.datanode.cache.revocation.polling.ms
description:
How often the DataNode should poll to see if the clients have
    stopped using a replica that the DataNode wants to uncache.

name: dfs.namenode.delegation.key.update-interval
description:
The update interval for master key for delegation tokens 
       in the namenode in milliseconds.

name: mapreduce.map.cpu.vcores
description:
The number of virtual cores to request from the scheduler for
  each map task.

name: dfs.qjournal.get-journal-state.timeout.ms
description:
Timeout in milliseconds when calling getJournalState().
    JournalNodes.

name: mapreduce.task.skip.start.attempts
description:
The number of Task attempts AFTER which skip mode
    will be kicked off. When skip mode is kicked off, the
    tasks reports the range of records which it will process
    next, to the MR ApplicationMaster. So that on failures, the MR AM
    knows which ones are possibly the bad records. On further executions,
    those are skipped.

name: dfs.client.refresh.read-block-locations.threads
description:
Number of threads to use for refreshing LocatedBlocks of registered
      DFSInputStreams. If a DFSClient opens many DFSInputStreams, increasing
      this may help refresh them all in a timely manner.
